# .clang-format - C/C++ formatting policy for the plants firmware.
# Tool: clang-format, pinned to v22.1.5 (the pre-commit mirror rev). Tuned to the
# existing firmware house style: 4-space indent, function brace on its own line,
# K&R control braces, 80 columns, pointer binds to the name.
#
# CHANGED-SCOPE, NEVER BULK (AGENTS.md §code-style + #120). The firmware carries
# intentional manual column alignment; a full-tree reformat would destroy it. So
# clang-format runs on NEW / CHANGED files only (pre-commit hook + the CI step) —
# it is the one deliberate exception to the repo's otherwise --all-files gate.
#   just lint-fw            # check the C/C++ files you've changed vs main
#   just lint-fw --fix      # apply the formatting to them
#
# Idempotent with v22.1.5 (a second pass produces zero changes):
#   - AlignTrailingComments: Leave  -> keep existing trailing-comment columns as
#     written (never re-flow them into a new column => no oscillation, and the
#     hand-aligned columns survive an edit).
#   - ReflowComments: false         -> never re-wrap comment prose.
# Two LLVM-default behaviours otherwise re-format on every pass (#120).
---
Language: Cpp
BasedOnStyle: LLVM
IndentWidth: 4
TabWidth: 4
UseTab: Never
ColumnLimit: 80
BreakBeforeBraces: Linux
PointerAlignment: Right
AllowShortFunctionsOnASingleLine: None
AllowShortIfStatementsOnASingleLine: WithoutElse
AllowShortLoopsOnASingleLine: false
KeepEmptyLinesAtTheStartOfBlocks: false
SpaceAfterCStyleCast: false
AlignTrailingComments: Leave
ReflowComments: false
# Keep include order as written - C headers can be order-sensitive.
SortIncludes: false
